(firstQuint)Apremilast Treatment for Pruritus and Quality of Life in Scalp Psoriasis.

 The scalp is the most frequently affected body region in psoriasis.

 Scalp Psoriasis can impair the quality of life greatly due to pruritus.

 This is however not usually investigated as a primary outcome of treatments.

 This study will investigate the effects of apremilast on the pruritus and quality of life and other patient reported outcomes in patients with scalp psoriasis.

